 Response options allowed for respondents to indicate that (i) the husband
 took the decision alone, (ii) the wife took the decision alone, or (iii)
 both husband and wife took the decision jointly.
 With these responses, we constructed plot-level indicators for these three
 categories of decision-making and compared differences between treatment
 groups
